You still keep them up.
你还留着它们

368
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:24,080
They're still there.
还在那里

369
00:26:27,120 --> 00:26:30,400
I told a lie that day. Maybe the first lie of my whole life.
那天我说了一个谎言，也许是我一生中的第一个谎言

370
00:26:31,760 --> 00:26:33,320
"Mebrure," I said,
“ Mebrure，”我说，

371
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:35,120
"I'll make you happy."
我会让你幸福

372
00:26:36,800 --> 00:26:40,440
"Mebrure, take my hand, and let's get up off this bench,
“拉着我的手，让我们从凳子上站起来

373
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:45,800
and -excuse my French-let's get the fuck out of here."
让我们他妈的离开这里” 原谅我说了脏话

374
00:26:45,880 --> 00:26:47,080
Without a care in the world.
没有一点牵挂

375
00:26:48,960 --> 00:26:49,960
Or...
或者

376
00:26:51,560 --> 00:26:53,480
"Mebrure, forget you ever knew me..."
“宝贝，忘了你曾经认识我”

377
00:26:53,560 --> 00:26:55,800
I'm not made for marriage.
“我不是个适合结婚的人”

378
00:26:57,080 --> 00:26:58,800
"I'll only make you unhappy."
“我只会给你带来不幸”

379
00:27:00,040 --> 00:27:01,120
Something like that.
像这样

380
00:27:03,840 --> 00:27:06,320
You can't hold your liquor at all, can you?
你根本不能喝酒，是吗？

381
00:27:06,400 --> 00:27:08,440
You're already seeing double. Where are you...
你已经看重影了，你在哪……

382
00:27:09,080 --> 00:27:11,400
Go talk to her. Go on.
去跟她聊天吧

383
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:15,320
Think about what you're going to say. You'll kick yourself later otherwise.
想好了再说话，不然你会后悔的

384
00:27:24,080 --> 00:27:26,120
A miserable soul, desperate for attention.
一个悲惨的灵魂，渴望得到关注

385
00:27:27,760 --> 00:27:31,320
The biggest favor you can do for such a sociopath is to talk about him.
你能为这样的反社会变态做的最大的帮助就是谈论他

386
00:27:32,160 --> 00:27:35,640
But you've been on this case ever since the murders started.
但是，自谋杀案发生以来，您一直在关注这个案件

387
00:27:35,720 --> 00:27:37,640
Isn't that a favor to him, then?
那不是对他有利吗？

388
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:39,400
I'm a journalist.
我是记者

389
00:27:39,480 --> 00:27:41,800
I have to inform the public.
我必须通知公众

390
00:27:41,880 --> 00:27:45,240
Ates, aren't you afraid at all that the murderer will target you?
Ates，你一点都不害怕凶手会把你作为目标吗？

391
00:27:46,960 --> 00:27:48,440
Look...
看

392
00:27:48,520 --> 00:27:50,040
Just like he has his eyes on me,
就像他看着我一样

393
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:52,640
I have my eyes on the perimeter of my house.
我也能在房子周围看到你

394
00:27:54,440 --> 00:27:56,920
Remember, no one can turn invisible.
记住，没有人可以隐身

395
00:27:57,000 --> 00:28:02,480
Least of all someone so deranged.
至少如此疯狂的人不会

396
00:28:12,640 --> 00:28:14,400
This is what I do, you see.
这就是我所做的，你看到了吗

397
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:18,160
I'm in show business.
我在做演员

398
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:22,200
The show serves one purpose only... To make people forget.
表演只不过是为了让人们忘记

399
00:28:22,760 --> 00:28:24,240
I'm in the forgetting business.
我正在忘记事情

400
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:28,000
- You're being too harsh on yourself. - It's how it works.
-你对自己太苛刻了-这就是它的运作方式

401
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:30,640
Let's say there's a massacre somewhere.
假设某处发生大屠杀

402
00:28:31,560 --> 00:28:34,080
There's an assassination, but the assassin never gets caught.
发生一次暗杀，但刺客从未被抓住

403
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:35,520
I make people forget about them.
我能让人们忘记他们

404
00:28:36,080 --> 00:28:40,920
Has there been a huge fraud? Call for me and I'll make them forget.
发生过大型诈骗案吗？找我，我会让他们忘记

405
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:43,400
How? How do you make them forget?
怎么做？如何使他们忘记？

406
00:28:43,480 --> 00:28:47,320
With stories such as this one about the murderer.
像这样一个关于凶手的故事

407
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:49,880
I spin a fairy tale.
我编了一个童话故事

408
00:28:49,960 --> 00:28:52,040
They all listen with bated breath.
大家都屏息静听

409
00:28:53,240 --> 00:28:55,240
He gets caught and another one emerges.
他被抓了之后另一个人出现了

410
00:28:55,320 --> 00:28:57,760
He gets caught, and another one.
又被抓了，然后又出现一个

411
00:28:57,840 --> 00:29:01,440
I tell all their stories. But you know what I don't do?
我给他们讲故事，但是你知道我不做什么吗？

412
00:29:02,600 --> 00:29:05,640
How come so many people are licensed to carry guns?
为什么这么多人可以携带枪支?

413
00:29:05,720 --> 00:29:09,160
How come people can access guns so easily?
为什么人们可以如此轻易地获得枪支?

414
00:29:09,240 --> 00:29:11,160
I never talk about that.
我从没说过

415
00:29:12,400 --> 00:29:13,480
You got it?
你明白了吗？

416
00:29:16,160 --> 00:29:18,440
If you want to make people forget about the gun,
如果你想让人们忘记枪

417
00:29:19,120 --> 00:29:22,480
all you have to do is talk about the victim.
你所要做的就是谈论受害者

418
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:30,680
But I'm not doing it anymore.
但我不再这样做了

419
00:29:32,360 --> 00:29:34,720
I've had it up to here.
到此为止

420
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:39,160
What will you do?
你会怎么做？

421
00:29:41,280 --> 00:29:42,520
May I curse?
我可以讲脏话吗？

422
00:29:46,520 --> 00:29:48,520
I'll fuck them up.
我会干他妈的

423
00:29:48,600 --> 00:29:50,320
I won't let people forget.
我不会让人们忘记

424
00:29:52,040 --> 00:29:53,720
When did you decide on that?
你什么时候决定的?

425
00:29:54,440 --> 00:29:55,640
Today.
今天

426
00:29:55,720 --> 00:29:58,040
As I was shooting you, to be precise.
准确地说，当我给你拍照时

427
00:30:29,640 --> 00:30:32,080
You're so sweet.
你好骚啊

428
00:30:54,120 --> 00:30:55,120
The car...
车！

429
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:12,520
Zuhal...

430
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:14,680
I've been thinking.
我一直在想

431
00:32:15,320 --> 00:32:17,960
We should get you a place.
我们应该给你找个地方

432
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:20,280
A place of your own.
属于你自己的地方

433
00:32:20,360 --> 00:32:23,240
You'd both be more comfortable that way.
那样你们俩会更舒服

434
00:32:23,320 --> 00:32:25,640
He'll have his own room, at least.
他至少会有自己的房间

435
00:32:25,720 --> 00:32:28,440
I can cover the rent until you get a job.
我能负担租金直到你找到工作

436
00:32:29,080 --> 00:32:34,760
When you said you'd been thinking, I thought you'd be like...
当你说你一直在想的时候，我以为你会像

437
00:32:34,840 --> 00:32:38,800
"Let's sell the apartment downstairs and get you a place of your own."
“我把楼下的公寓卖了，给你找个地方住。”

438
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:40,440
Something like that.
像这样

439
00:32:42,640 --> 00:32:44,840
It's not like I haven't been doing that.
我不是没想过

440
00:32:44,920 --> 00:32:47,080
Number four, covered your high school.
四号房间，用于支付你高中的费用

441
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:49,920
Number six, your college.
六号，大学的费用

442
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:53,000
Number seven, your master's in London.
七号，你的伦敦硕士学位

443
00:32:53,080 --> 00:32:56,600
Number three, as you know, went towards your mother's treatment.
如你所知，三号支付了你母亲的治疗费用

444
00:32:56,680 --> 00:32:59,040
I'm all alone in this huge building now.
我现在一个人在这个巨大的大楼里

445
00:33:00,960 --> 00:33:06,600
- We still have Number eight, though. - I told you I rent that out.
-不过我们还有八号 -我告诉你我把它租出去了

446
00:33:07,560 --> 00:33:12,880
We can tell the tenants we need to sell it. I can talk to them.
我们可以告诉租户我们需要卖掉，可以和他们交谈

447
00:33:12,960 --> 00:33:15,560
You can't talk to them. They're using it for storage.
不能跟他们谈，他们在用房间做仓库

448
00:33:15,640 --> 00:33:17,080
They live abroad.
他们住在国外

449
00:33:17,160 --> 00:33:20,520
I can call them, then. Just give me their number.
我可以打电话给他们，给我他们的电话

450
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:23,600
Of course. We can sell this apartment, as well.
当然我们也可以卖这套公寓

451
00:33:23,680 --> 00:33:25,440
You can put me in a home.
你可以把我放在家里

452
00:33:25,520 --> 00:33:27,320
Even better, you can put me out on the street.
也可以把我扔到大街上

453
00:33:28,160 --> 00:33:30,280
Do you realize how selfish you sound?
你知道你听起来有多自私吗？

454
00:33:30,880 --> 00:33:33,720
This building is named after your mother.
这座建筑以你母亲的名字命名

455
00:33:34,280 --> 00:33:36,000
How can you be so ready to let it go?
你怎么能这么轻易放手？

456
00:33:37,040 --> 00:33:39,840
We should be grateful to my departed grandfather, right?
我们应该感谢我已故的祖父，对吗？

457
00:33:40,400 --> 00:33:43,080
For giving this building to my mother.
谢谢他把这栋楼交给我妈妈

458
00:33:43,160 --> 00:33:45,360
What would we do if he hadn't?
如果没有他我们该怎么办？

459
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:49,440
What would you do? What would I? What would Deva?
你怎么办？我怎么办？Deva怎么办？

460
00:33:50,120 --> 00:33:51,440
Say what you mean to say.
说出来

461
00:33:52,240 --> 00:33:54,520
What is it you'd like to say, exactly?
您到底想说什么？

462
00:33:56,040 --> 00:33:58,520
Don't stick your nose where it doesn't belong.
不要多管闲事

463
00:33:59,800 --> 00:34:02,160
See how I don't stick my nose into your business?
学学我，从不多管闲事

464
00:34:02,240 --> 00:34:06,440
See how I never ask about why you got divorced from your husband?
我从没问过你为什么与丈夫离婚？

465
00:34:06,520 --> 00:34:09,120
See how I keep my mouth shut? How about you try it out for once?
学我怎么闭嘴，你尝试一下如何？

466
00:34:09,200 --> 00:34:10,440
Ask me, dad.
问我啊

467
00:34:11,280 --> 00:34:13,640
Ask me. Why don't you?
问什么不问呢？

468
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:16,120
Why don't you ask?
你为什么不问？

469
00:34:18,680 --> 00:34:22,840
Ask me why Deva and I came here.
问我为什么Deva和我来这里

470
00:34:22,920 --> 00:34:25,440
Ask me why he wants to get divorced.
问我为什么他要离婚

471
00:34:26,640 --> 00:34:29,200
Come on! But you won't, will you?
来吧！但是你不会问，对吗？

472
00:34:29,280 --> 00:34:31,040
You know why you won't?
你知道为什么你不会问吗？

473
00:34:31,120 --> 00:34:34,760
Because you hate listening to other people's problems.
因为你讨厌听别人的问题

474
00:34:34,840 --> 00:34:37,280
It's the thing you hate the most.
这是你最讨厌的事情

475
00:34:37,360 --> 00:34:40,160
Someone telling you of their troubles.
别人告诉你他们的麻烦事

476
00:34:41,120 --> 00:34:42,120
Dad...
爸

477
00:34:42,680 --> 00:34:46,520
You can't even bear it when people are sick around you.
你甚至不能忍受周围的人生病

478
00:34:47,080 --> 00:34:50,160
Remember the times I had fevers as a kid?
还记得我小时候发烧吗？

479
00:34:50,240 --> 00:34:53,600
Remember what you did? Do you remember?
记得你做了什么吗？

480
00:34:53,680 --> 00:34:56,480
I'll remind you. You left.
我来提醒你！你离开了！

481
00:34:57,520 --> 00:34:59,560
You left the house.
你离开了家

482
00:34:59,640 --> 00:35:03,120
I used to pray with all my might not to get sick.
我曾经尽力祈祷不生病

483
00:35:03,200 --> 00:35:06,240
Not to get fevers so that my father didn't get mad at me.
不要发烧，这样我的父亲就不会生我的气

484
00:35:07,080 --> 00:35:08,560
You didn't look after mom, either.
你也没照顾妈妈

485
00:35:09,120 --> 00:35:12,520
The nurses did. I did. father didn't get mad at me.
护士照顾了，我和医生照顾了

486
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:14,840
But you never did.
但是你从来没有

487
00:35:14,920 --> 00:35:17,040
You'd come to the hospital.
你去医院

488
00:35:17,120 --> 00:35:19,640
I'd tell you, "Dad, mom's dying."
我会告诉你，“爸爸，妈妈快死了”

489
00:35:19,720 --> 00:35:21,160
You'd say "No."
你会说“不”

490
00:35:21,240 --> 00:35:24,120
"She's doing great. Mom's doing great."
“她很好，妈妈很好”

491
00:35:24,200 --> 00:35:26,280
Because that's what you want to hear.
因为那是你想听到的

492
00:35:27,160 --> 00:35:29,920
Everything's great. No problems whatsoever.
一切都很好没有任何问题

493
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:32,600
Everything's perfect.
一切都很完美

494
00:35:32,680 --> 00:35:37,320
I'll say it if it will help. We have no problems, dad.
如果有用的话，我就说出来  我们没问题，爸爸

495
00:35:38,640 --> 00:35:42,120
You're perfect. I'm perfect.
你是完美的  我是完美的

496
00:35:42,200 --> 00:35:44,080
Deva's perfect.
Deva也是完美的

497
00:35:44,160 --> 00:35:45,760
Life's perfect.
完美的人生

498
00:35:49,760 --> 00:35:50,760
Good.
好

499
00:35:51,440 --> 00:35:52,560
That's good.
那很好

500
00:36:05,160 --> 00:36:06,720
Agah Beyoglu.
这里是Agha Beyoglu

501
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:09,360
- Agah? - Nukhet!
-Agah？-Nukhet！

502
00:36:09,440 --> 00:36:10,960
How are you?
你好吗？

503
00:36:11,480 --> 00:36:13,520
I was just thinking about you.
我刚刚还在想你

504
00:36:13,600 --> 00:36:15,160
I was able to find some tickets.
我搞到了几张票

505
00:36:15,240 --> 00:36:18,560
- Were you now? - It's tonight. Would you like to join me?
-是吗？-今天晚上你想一起吗？

506
00:36:18,640 --> 00:36:19,720
Sure.
当然

507
00:36:26,040 --> 00:36:28,240
- What is it? - We're ready.
-什么事？-我们准备好了

508
00:36:28,320 --> 00:36:29,480
I'll be right there.
我马上到

509
00:36:44,280 --> 00:36:46,160
Hand these out to the guys.
把这些交给他们

510
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:53,880
Alright...
好了……

511
00:36:55,920 --> 00:36:57,000
Where's Nevra?
Nevra呢？

512
00:36:57,640 --> 00:37:01,000
She got a tip from somewhere. She went to the courthouse to look into it.
她从某个地方得到了线报，去了法院进行调查

513
00:37:01,600 --> 00:37:04,000
You know Mehmet Yurtgil, the judge?
你知道Mehmet Yurtgil吗？

514
00:37:04,080 --> 00:37:05,640
He was known for taking bribes.
他因受贿而闻名

515
00:37:06,200 --> 00:37:08,240
She's looking into the suspects that were wronged.
她在调查被冤枉的嫌疑犯

516
00:37:08,320 --> 00:37:11,960
She thinks someone might've took revenge on him.
她认为有人可能会对他报仇

517
00:37:12,720 --> 00:37:14,520
Alright then. Anyway,
好吧，不管怎样

518
00:37:15,080 --> 00:37:18,240
I have the ballistics report right here. Here's the situation:
我这里有弹道报告，结果是这样：

519
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:22,000
The gun that was used to kill Naimhan Turedi
用来杀死Naimhan Turedi的枪

520
00:37:22,080 --> 00:37:24,560
does not match the one used to kill Mehmet Yurtgil.
与用来杀死Mehmet Yurtgil的那只不匹配

521
00:37:24,640 --> 00:37:28,480
That gun wasn't registered anywhere. However...
那枪没有在任何地方注册

522
00:37:28,560 --> 00:37:32,040
We have some leads on the gun that was used to kill Naimhan Turedi.
我们在用来杀死Naimhan Turedi的枪上有一些线索

523
00:37:32,120 --> 00:37:35,920
Someone was shot and wounded with that gun in 2001.
2001年有人用那把枪开枪并受伤

524
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:37,600
The gun was seized, and is supposed to be
枪应该是被没收了

525
00:37:37,640 --> 00:37:43,080
in the Ard?chan municipality police department's evidence locker.
存放在Ard?chan市警察局的证据储物柜中

526
00:37:43,160 --> 00:37:45,320
But it's gone! Why's that?
但是它消失了，为什么呢？

527
00:37:45,400 --> 00:37:48,120
Because that evidence locker no longer exists.
因为那个证据储物柜已经没有了

528
00:37:49,120 --> 00:37:51,680
How about... That sleazeball you were looking into?
你调查的那个混蛋怎么样？

529
00:37:51,760 --> 00:37:54,000
He had nothing to do with it.
他跟这些都没有关系

530
00:37:55,440 --> 00:37:56,960
Alright. Now...
好吧……

531
00:37:58,120 --> 00:38:00,600
The individual who did all this shit...
做这些事的人

532
00:38:00,680 --> 00:38:04,120
Let's call him Tufan for now.
我们暂时叫他Tufan

533
00:38:04,200 --> 00:38:07,080
Tufan gets into the evidence locker.
Tufan进入证据储物柜

534
00:38:07,840 --> 00:38:10,680
He burglarizes the locker. Then...
他盗窃了储物柜，然后

535
00:38:10,760 --> 00:38:14,080
He burns the place down to make it look like the mafia did it.
他把地方烧了，使它看起来像黑手党做的一样

536
00:38:15,040 --> 00:38:18,120
So he's not interested in killing just anyone.
所以他对杀人不感兴趣

537
00:38:18,200 --> 00:38:20,200
He's not a regular serial killer.
他不是常规的连环杀手

538
00:38:20,280 --> 00:38:21,890
Since he's in possession of so many guns,
既然他拥有这么多枪，

539
00:38:21,920 --> 00:38:24,400
and assuming he's not interested in selling them,
并假设他不准备卖枪

540
00:38:24,480 --> 00:38:26,480
welcome to your own personal hells.
那么就很明显了

541
00:38:27,640 --> 00:38:29,200
He's going to commit a massacre.
他将要开始屠杀

542
00:38:33,240 --> 00:38:35,160
Unless we catch him first.
